        Product Description

        Yonex introduces some exciting updates to their EZONE racquet line for 2022. This new 7th generation EZONE racquet series has updated the 2020 version. Like previous generations of the Yonex EZONE 98 7th Gen; the racquet remains an easy-swinging player’s frame that offers excellent feel, spin, and stability. The Yonex EZONE 98 7th Gen Tennis Racquet comes with a striking new blue colorway update. Take to the court today with the “Easy One”. Yonex implements 2G-NAMD Speed graphite into the frame provides enhanced ball speed without sacrificing comfort. Yonex updated the shaft design for improved stability and power. The thicker shaft structure with a convex design reduces unwanted racquet torque on off-centered shots for added power. The Yonex EZONE 98 7th Gen Tennis Racquet includes Vibration Dampening Mesh within the handle of the frame which helps reduce shock. Overall, the EZONE 98 7th Gen places power firmly into the players’ hands, allowing for additional ball speed. This frame is an impressive option for the intermediate to advanced player with a faster swing, looking for excellent feel, spin, stability, and precision.

            How customer reviews and ratings work

            Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

            To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

            Michael S.
            5.0 out of 5 stars Great mobility, decent power, nice color
            Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2022
            Grip Size: 4-1/8
            I'm a recreational player. Spending over $200 on a racquet is a lot but the craftsmanship from Yonex, Japan is top notch.

            Mine came with 16g synthetic gut prestrung and I spent about two hours with this racquet. It feels very comfortable and easy to use.

            I'm coming from Prince and Head racquets that weigh more than this in midplus sizes so I will have to adjust over time.

            This one is a keeper for the color details alone. Really awesome paint job and I look forward to improving my tennis game with it.

            This isn't the best for folks that are used to the power of bigger racquets but it's also not super demanding either. Grab the Ezone 100 if you want more power. As for me, this Ezone 98 has a nice balance of control and power. It also feels super maneuverable. Excellent quality. Recommended.
